System Information
 uname -a: Show system info
 hostname: Show/set system hostname
 uptime: Show system uptime
 top / htop: Show running processes
 df -h: Show disk usage
 free -h: Show memory usage
 lsblk: List block devices
 lscpu: CPU architecture info
 lsusb: List USB devices
 lspci: List PCI devices
 whoami: Current user
----------------------------------------------------
 File and Directory Management
 ls: List files
 cd: Change directory
 pwd: Print working directory
 mkdir: Make directory
 rmdir: Remove empty directory
 rm: Remove file/directory
 cp: Copy file/directory
 mv: Move/rename file
 touch: Create empty file
 find: Search for files
----------------------------------------------------
 File Viewing and Editing
 cat: View file content
 less / more: Page through file content
 head / tail: View beginning/end of file
 nano: Simple text editor
 vim: Advanced text editor
 grep: Search text in files
----------------------------------------------------
 Searching and Filtering
 grep: Search text
find: Find files/directories
 locate: Fast file search
 which: Path of command
 whereis: Locate binary/source/man
----------------------------------------------------
 File Permissions
 chmod: Change file permissions
 chown: Change file owner
 ls -l: List files with permissions
----------------------------------------------------
 Package Management
 sudo apt update: Update package list (Debian/Ubuntu)
 sudo apt install <pkg>: Install package (Debian/Ubuntu)
 sudo dnf install <pkg>: Install package (Fedora/RHEL)
 sudo pacman -Syu: Update system (Arch)
----------------------------------------------------
 User Management
 who / w: Who is logged in
 id: Current user ID
 adduser / useradd: Add a new user
 passwd: Change user password
 usermod: Modify user
 deluser / userdel: Delete user
----------------------------------------------------
 Networking
 ip a / ifconfig: Show IP addresses
 ping: Check network connection
 traceroute: Trace network path
 netstat -tuln: List open ports
 curl / wget: Download from web
 ssh: Remote login
 scp: Secure copy
----------------------------------------------------
 Process Management
 ps aux: List processes
 top: Live process viewer
kill <pid>: Kill process by PID
 killall <name>: Kill process by name
 nice / renice: Set process priority
 Disk and Storage
 df -h: Disk usage
 du -sh: Directory size
 mount / umount: Mount/unmount filesystem
 fdisk / parted: Partition disks
 mkfs / fsck: Filesystem tools
----------------------------------------------------
 Miscellaneous
 alias: Create command shortcuts
 history: Show command history
 echo: Display message
 date: Show/set date
 cal: Calendar
 man: Command manual
 clear: Clear terminal
